  "title": "QAQC Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title:</strong> Facilities Addition & Alteration (A&A) Projects Manager / QAQC Manager</p><p><strong>Overview:</strong><br />We are looking for a detail-oriented and proactive professional to manage Addition & Alteration (A&A) projects within a large mixed-use development. This role focuses on planning, coordinating, and delivering A&A works, ensuring full compliance with statutory requirements, contractual obligations, and high-quality standards. The successful candidate will collaborate closely with internal stakeholders, consultants, and contractors to execute projects safely, on schedule, and within budget.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Plan, manage, and execute A&A projects from inception to completion, covering scope definition, budgeting, scheduling, and resource allocation.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with consultants, contractors, and vendors to ensure timely delivery of project milestones.</p></li><li><p>Review and validate project drawings, specifications, method statements, and risk assessments.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with Singapore statutory and regulatory requirements (e.g., BCA, SCDF, MOM, NEA, PUB).</p></li><li><p>Obtain necessary permits and approvals for A&A works.</p></li><li><p>Monitor project progress, quality, and safety standards through regular site inspections.</p></li><li><p>Identify and resolve project issues, defects, and non-conformances promptly.</p></li><li><p>Prepare project reports, cost tracking, and dashboards for management review.</p></li><li><p>Manage handover documentation and ensure seamless integration with existing facilities.</p></li><li><p>Promote a strong culture of safety, compliance, and service excellence throughout project execution.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Building Services, Mechanical/Electrical Engineering, Facilities Management, or related discipline.</p></li><li><p>3–5 years of experience in A&A projects, facilities management, or building operations.</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of architectural and building systems (ACMV, electrical, plumbing, fire safety) and construction processes.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with Singapore codes of practice and statutory submission requirements.</p></li><li><p>Experience using project management tools and facilities management documentation systems.</p></li><li><p>Excellent coordination, communication, and documentation skills.</p></li><li><p>Ability to manage multiple projects within a large-scale, 24/7 operational environment.</p></li><li><p>Professional certifications (FSM, ISO Auditor, Green Mark, Project Management) are advantageous.</p></li></ul>",
